A suitable path object on sections to a fixed function r\colon  A \to  B is given by a contravariant sum of path objects \mathchoice {\textstyle \int _{  \mathopen {}\left \lparen s:\mathchoice {\textstyle \prod _{  \mathopen {}\left \lparen x:B\right \rparen \mathclose {} }}{\textstyle \prod _{  \mathopen {}\left \lparen x:B\right \rparen \mathclose {} }}{\scriptstyle \prod _{  \mathopen {}\left \lparen x:B\right \rparen \mathclose {} }}{\scriptscriptstyle \prod _{  \mathopen {}\left \lparen x:B\right \rparen \mathclose {} }}\mathord {\vartriangle }A\right \rparen \mathclose {} }}{\textstyle \int _{  \mathopen {}\left \lparen s:\mathchoice {\textstyle \prod _{  \mathopen {}\left \lparen x:B\right \rparen \mathclose {} }}{\textstyle \prod _{  \mathopen {}\left \lparen x:B\right \rparen \mathclose {} }}{\scriptstyle \prod _{  \mathopen {}\left \lparen x:B\right \rparen \mathclose {} }}{\scriptscriptstyle \prod _{  \mathopen {}\left \lparen x:B\right \rparen \mathclose {} }}\mathord {\vartriangle }A\right \rparen \mathclose {} }}{\scriptstyle \int _{  \mathopen {}\left \lparen s:\mathchoice {\textstyle \prod _{  \mathopen {}\left \lparen x:B\right \rparen \mathclose {} }}{\textstyle \prod _{  \mathopen {}\left \lparen x:B\right \rparen \mathclose {} }}{\scriptstyle \prod _{  \mathopen {}\left \lparen x:B\right \rparen \mathclose {} }}{\scriptscriptstyle \prod _{  \mathopen {}\left \lparen x:B\right \rparen \mathclose {} }}\mathord {\vartriangle }A\right \rparen \mathclose {} }}{\scriptscriptstyle \int _{  \mathopen {}\left \lparen s:\mathchoice {\textstyle \prod _{  \mathopen {}\left \lparen x:B\right \rparen \mathclose {} }}{\textstyle \prod _{  \mathopen {}\left \lparen x:B\right \rparen \mathclose {} }}{\scriptstyle \prod _{  \mathopen {}\left \lparen x:B\right \rparen \mathclose {} }}{\scriptscriptstyle \prod _{  \mathopen {}\left \lparen x:B\right \rparen \mathclose {} }}\mathord {\vartriangle }A\right \rparen \mathclose {} }}r\circ  s \sim  1_{B}, as sectionhood witnesses form a right-cloven family over their underlying sections (). In particular, an isomorphism of sections of r from 
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen s,h\right \rparen \mathclose {}
 to 
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen s',h'\right \rparen \mathclose {}
 is given by a homotopy H_s \colon  s \sim  s' together with a higher homotopy H_h \colon  h \sim    \mathopen {}\left \lparen \lambda {x}\mathpunct {.}\mathsf {act}_{r}  \mathopen {}\left \lparen H_s x\right \rparen \mathclose {} \cdot  h'x\right \rparen \mathclose {} .

A suitable path object on retractions to a fixed function s\colon  B \to  A is given by a contravariant sum of path objects  \mathchoice {\textstyle \int _{  \mathopen {}\left \lparen r:\mathchoice {\textstyle \prod _{  \mathopen {}\left \lparen x:A\right \rparen \mathclose {} }}{\textstyle \prod _{  \mathopen {}\left \lparen x:A\right \rparen \mathclose {} }}{\scriptstyle \prod _{  \mathopen {}\left \lparen x:A\right \rparen \mathclose {} }}{\scriptscriptstyle \prod _{  \mathopen {}\left \lparen x:A\right \rparen \mathclose {} }}\mathord {\vartriangle }B\right \rparen \mathclose {} }}{\textstyle \int _{  \mathopen {}\left \lparen r:\mathchoice {\textstyle \prod _{  \mathopen {}\left \lparen x:A\right \rparen \mathclose {} }}{\textstyle \prod _{  \mathopen {}\left \lparen x:A\right \rparen \mathclose {} }}{\scriptstyle \prod _{  \mathopen {}\left \lparen x:A\right \rparen \mathclose {} }}{\scriptscriptstyle \prod _{  \mathopen {}\left \lparen x:A\right \rparen \mathclose {} }}\mathord {\vartriangle }B\right \rparen \mathclose {} }}{\scriptstyle \int _{  \mathopen {}\left \lparen r:\mathchoice {\textstyle \prod _{  \mathopen {}\left \lparen x:A\right \rparen \mathclose {} }}{\textstyle \prod _{  \mathopen {}\left \lparen x:A\right \rparen \mathclose {} }}{\scriptstyle \prod _{  \mathopen {}\left \lparen x:A\right \rparen \mathclose {} }}{\scriptscriptstyle \prod _{  \mathopen {}\left \lparen x:A\right \rparen \mathclose {} }}\mathord {\vartriangle }B\right \rparen \mathclose {} }}{\scriptscriptstyle \int _{  \mathopen {}\left \lparen r:\mathchoice {\textstyle \prod _{  \mathopen {}\left \lparen x:A\right \rparen \mathclose {} }}{\textstyle \prod _{  \mathopen {}\left \lparen x:A\right \rparen \mathclose {} }}{\scriptstyle \prod _{  \mathopen {}\left \lparen x:A\right \rparen \mathclose {} }}{\scriptscriptstyle \prod _{  \mathopen {}\left \lparen x:A\right \rparen \mathclose {} }}\mathord {\vartriangle }B\right \rparen \mathclose {} }}r\circ  s \sim  1_{B}, as retractionhood witnesses form a right-cloven family over their underlying sections (). In particular, an isomorphism of retractions of s from 
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen r,h\right \rparen \mathclose {}
 to 
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen r',h'\right \rparen \mathclose {}
 is given by a homotopy H_r \colon  r \sim  r' together with a higher homotopy H_h \colon  h \sim    \mathopen {}\left \lparen \lambda {x}\mathpunct {.}H_r  \mathopen {}\left \lparen r x\right \rparen \mathclose {} \cdot  h'x\right \rparen \mathclose {} .

A suitable path object on retractions to a fixed function s\colon  B \to  A is given by a contravariant sum of path objects  \mathchoice {\textstyle \int _{  \mathopen {}\left \lparen r:\mathchoice {\textstyle \prod _{  \mathopen {}\left \lparen x:A\right \rparen \mathclose {} }}{\textstyle \prod _{  \mathopen {}\left \lparen x:A\right \rparen \mathclose {} }}{\scriptstyle \prod _{  \mathopen {}\left \lparen x:A\right \rparen \mathclose {} }}{\scriptscriptstyle \prod _{  \mathopen {}\left \lparen x:A\right \rparen \mathclose {} }}\mathord {\vartriangle }B\right \rparen \mathclose {} }}{\textstyle \int _{  \mathopen {}\left \lparen r:\mathchoice {\textstyle \prod _{  \mathopen {}\left \lparen x:A\right \rparen \mathclose {} }}{\textstyle \prod _{  \mathopen {}\left \lparen x:A\right \rparen \mathclose {} }}{\scriptstyle \prod _{  \mathopen {}\left \lparen x:A\right \rparen \mathclose {} }}{\scriptscriptstyle \prod _{  \mathopen {}\left \lparen x:A\right \rparen \mathclose {} }}\mathord {\vartriangle }B\right \rparen \mathclose {} }}{\scriptstyle \int _{  \mathopen {}\left \lparen r:\mathchoice {\textstyle \prod _{  \mathopen {}\left \lparen x:A\right \rparen \mathclose {} }}{\textstyle \prod _{  \mathopen {}\left \lparen x:A\right \rparen \mathclose {} }}{\scriptstyle \prod _{  \mathopen {}\left \lparen x:A\right \rparen \mathclose {} }}{\scriptscriptstyle \prod _{  \mathopen {}\left \lparen x:A\right \rparen \mathclose {} }}\mathord {\vartriangle }B\right \rparen \mathclose {} }}{\scriptscriptstyle \int _{  \mathopen {}\left \lparen r:\mathchoice {\textstyle \prod _{  \mathopen {}\left \lparen x:A\right \rparen \mathclose {} }}{\textstyle \prod _{  \mathopen {}\left \lparen x:A\right \rparen \mathclose {} }}{\scriptstyle \prod _{  \mathopen {}\left \lparen x:A\right \rparen \mathclose {} }}{\scriptscriptstyle \prod _{  \mathopen {}\left \lparen x:A\right \rparen \mathclose {} }}\mathord {\vartriangle }B\right \rparen \mathclose {} }}r\circ  s \sim  1_{B}, as retractionhood witnesses form a right-cloven family over their underlying sections (). In particular, an isomorphism of retractions of s from 
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen r,h\right \rparen \mathclose {}
 to 
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen r',h'\right \rparen \mathclose {}
 is given by a homotopy H_r \colon  r \sim  r' together with a higher homotopy H_h \colon  h \sim    \mathopen {}\left \lparen \lambda {x}\mathpunct {.}H_r  \mathopen {}\left \lparen r x\right \rparen \mathclose {} \cdot  h'x\right \rparen \mathclose {} .

Let s \colon  B \to  A and r \colon  A \to  B be a pair of maps. A homotopy h \colon  r\circ  s \sim  1_{B} exhibits s as a section of r and r as a retraction of s. Together, 
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen s,r\right \rparen \mathclose {}
 are referred to as a section-retraction pair.
